1
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:07,950
[A Prime Minister's Disguise]

2
00:01:08,170 --> 00:01:10,840
[Episode 12]

3
00:01:11,590 --> 00:01:13,070
-Bravo!
-Bravo!

4
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:15,500
Her Ladyship is back!

5
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:16,640
My Lady.

6
00:01:16,789 --> 00:01:17,350
Uncle Liu.

7
00:01:17,350 --> 00:01:18,870
-You're back.
-The moment I heard your loud voice,

8
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:20,289
I knew I was home.

9
00:01:20,310 --> 00:01:21,640
Come on, give that to me.

10
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:23,940
Ling'er.

11
00:01:28,150 --> 00:01:30,039
This girl...

12
00:01:30,060 --> 00:01:33,720
Now that I have a sister-in-law,
I've forgotten about my brother.

13
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:34,820
Yunqing,

14
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:36,440
I begged the Empress Dowager

15
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:37,380
for a long time

16
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:38,350
before she finally agreed

17
00:01:38,350 --> 00:01:39,720
to let me come home quietly.

18
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:41,840
But we've only been apart for...

19
00:01:43,420 --> 00:01:44,539
Stop counting.

20
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,560
I just missed you.

21
00:01:45,979 --> 00:01:47,130
It's so lively here.

22
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:48,220
What are you doing?

23
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:49,580
Watching Miss Jiang practice swordsmanship.

24
00:01:49,580 --> 00:01:50,610
Her skills

25
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:51,400
are truly remarkable.

26
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,460
Of course they are.

27
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:54,320
Alright, that's enough.

28
00:01:55,470 --> 00:01:56,850
It's good to be home.

29
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,759
Uncle Liu.

30
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,340
Come and have

31
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:03,590
some buns, your favorite.

32
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:04,430
I brought them over

33
00:02:04,430 --> 00:02:05,960
straight from the steamer.

34
00:02:07,130 --> 00:02:08,860
Don't just grab them like that!

35
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,720
It's been so long since we last met.

36
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:12,720
Shall we catch up?

37
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:21,890
Don't just focus on eating.

38
00:02:21,890 --> 00:02:23,820
Don't forget what you promised me.

39
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,920
That year, on your sixteenth birthday,

40
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,710
that was the first time I met you.

41
00:02:33,710 --> 00:02:35,260
I brought you a gift, remember?

42
00:02:35,260 --> 00:02:36,590
Even then, I knew

43
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:37,190
we'd become

44
00:02:37,190 --> 00:02:38,120
good friends.

45
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:39,670
Even if

46
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:40,710
you and my brother

47
00:02:40,710 --> 00:02:42,410
hadn't fallen for each other later,

48
00:02:42,410 --> 00:02:43,370
I believe

49
00:02:43,470 --> 00:02:44,530
we would still have

50
00:02:44,550 --> 00:02:45,870
become close friends.

51
00:02:45,910 --> 00:02:46,860
Right?

52
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,280
Yes.

53
00:03:08,010 --> 00:03:09,490
Why are you eating so fast?

54
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,520
Are you a soldier?

55
00:03:10,830 --> 00:03:11,600
Am I?

56
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:13,140
And you,

57
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:15,380
don't you like the food?

58
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:17,010
Why aren't you eating at all?

59
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:17,960
It's not that.

60
00:03:18,210 --> 00:03:19,000
Maybe it's because

61
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,740
I've been out in the world for so long

62
00:03:20,740 --> 00:03:22,280
that the palace food

63
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,760
seems tasteless to me now.

64
00:03:24,990 --> 00:03:26,550
You're the Emperor now,

65
00:03:26,570 --> 00:03:27,470
staying in

66
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:29,120
Yongqian Palace every day.

67
00:03:29,190 --> 00:03:30,240
Are you really that busy

68
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,590
with state affairs?

69
00:03:31,890 --> 00:03:32,660
Recently,

70
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:35,710
I've indeed been busy with state affairs.

71
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,470
But you're right—

72
00:03:37,690 --> 00:03:39,190
I should practice martial arts more.

73
00:03:39,190 --> 00:03:40,280
I'm getting rusty.

74
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:40,980
Exactly.

75
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:42,400
You need to practice martial arts more.

76
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,770
Don't just sit around.

77
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:45,980
I'll walk around more

78
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:48,290
and not practice martial arts.

79
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:50,100
You should practice martial arts too.

80
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:52,550
But don't just practice inside the palace.

81
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:53,790
Otherwise, what you're practicing

82
00:03:53,790 --> 00:03:55,680
will be heartless swordsmanship.

83
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:56,000
Mother,

84
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,150
what exactly do you want me to do?

85
00:03:57,150 --> 00:03:58,150
Just tell me.

86
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,680
Don't you feel like

87
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,470
the palace

88
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:03,400
has been missing something lately?

89
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,030
It's Consort Yue.

90
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:05,150
She's been home for two days.

91
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:05,630
See?

92
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:07,750
Even your uncle noticed.

93
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:10,310
Consort Yue's been gone this long

94
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,400
and you haven't

95
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:12,660
gone to see her.

96
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,810
You think I don't want to go?

97
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:20,920
I'll go.

98
00:04:22,310 --> 00:04:24,560
I'm annoying people in the palace.

99
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,190
Alright, alright.

100
00:04:26,190 --> 00:04:26,870
What are you doing?

101
00:04:26,870 --> 00:04:27,930
What are you doing?

102
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,870
I'll take my dear nephew out for a walk.

103
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:33,190
-No need for that.
-No need for that.

104
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:33,870
Sit down!

105
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:36,190
I'm full,

106
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:37,000
Sister.

107
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:37,800
Eat a bit more.

108
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:44,010
[Prime Minister's Mansion]

109
00:04:44,010 --> 00:04:45,360
Several of your outfits

110
00:04:45,390 --> 00:04:46,260
got stained.

111
00:04:46,290 --> 00:04:47,310
The maid didn't notice

112
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:48,430
and tore a cuff.

113
00:04:48,450 --> 00:04:49,480
I've mended it for you.

114
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,280
Yue...

115
00:04:52,790 --> 00:04:54,200
Ling...

116
00:04:55,780 --> 00:04:56,790
er.

117
00:04:56,810 --> 00:04:57,420
Uncle Liu,

118
00:04:57,450 --> 00:04:58,520
thank you for taking care of me. We...

119
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:59,680
Uncle Liu,

120
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:01,160
you have a lot to do today.

121
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,890
Please go ahead with your work.

122
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,680
Uncle Liu, let me see you out.

123
00:05:08,650 --> 00:05:10,310
When exactly are you leaving?

124
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,750
Have you set a date?

125
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:13,750
Chi.

126
00:05:14,310 --> 00:05:15,490
I've decided.

127
00:05:16,310 --> 00:05:17,240
I'm not leaving.

128
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:19,840
Yue Ling'er!

129
00:05:20,870 --> 00:05:21,510
What did I

130
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:22,510
call you back for?

131
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:24,480
If you can't handle such
a small matter properly,

132
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,000
I'll send you back

133
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,330
to the palace tomorrow.

134
00:05:28,410 --> 00:05:29,510
Yunqing!

135
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:30,840
It's so early in the morning.

136
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,640
What are you making a fuss about?

137
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:33,800
Come, sit down.

138
00:05:34,570 --> 00:05:35,370
Right, Chi.

139
00:05:35,490 --> 00:05:36,590
Didn't you just say

140
00:05:36,630 --> 00:05:37,830
you had something to attend to?

141
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:38,390
Go ahead.

142
00:05:38,750 --> 00:05:39,560
I'm going to chat with Yunqing

143
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,310
for a while.

144
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:42,090
Did you sleep well last night?

145
00:05:46,070 --> 00:05:46,950
We're going to

146
00:05:46,970 --> 00:05:47,720
talk about

147
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:48,950
some girl stuff.

148
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:50,240
You want to join?

149
00:05:55,010 --> 00:05:55,820
You two chat.

150
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,280
Yunqing,

151
00:05:58,409 --> 00:05:59,740
while you're staying here,

152
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:01,890
treat it as your home.

153
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,240
Why are you here?

154
00:06:04,730 --> 00:06:06,460
I'm here to pick up Consort Yue.

155
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:08,690
Go ahead.

156
00:06:10,190 --> 00:06:10,880
Those two are so close that they could

157
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:12,570
even sleep in the same room at night.

158
00:06:12,570 --> 00:06:14,170
I doubt you can take her away.

159
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:15,510
He's like a shadow,

160
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:16,920
always clinging

161
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,160
to Ling'er.

162
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:21,520
Ling'er.

163
00:06:22,670 --> 00:06:23,550
Huo Jingheng?

164
00:06:24,670 --> 00:06:25,730
Mind your manners.

165
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:28,590
Yunqing,

166
00:06:28,610 --> 00:06:29,740
don't go over there.

167
00:06:35,159 --> 00:06:36,070
Yunqing,

168
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,610
this is the etiquette of Former Ning.

169
00:06:37,610 --> 00:06:39,409
Your hand gesture is incorrect.

170
00:06:40,710 --> 00:06:41,440
Please rise.

171
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,190
Ling'er,

172
00:06:45,390 --> 00:06:46,270
I brought you your favorite pastries

173
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:47,630
from the palace.

174
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,340
Well,

175
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:55,070
is there any hibiscus hawthorn cake?

176
00:06:55,070 --> 00:06:56,600
I don't remember the names,

177
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:57,600
but there are

178
00:06:57,620 --> 00:06:58,480
red ones, blue ones,

179
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,800
green ones, purple ones—

180
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,000
all kinds of colors.

181
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:06,960
The red ones

182
00:07:06,980 --> 00:07:08,420
are hibiscus hawthorn cakes.

183
00:07:08,420 --> 00:07:09,300
The yellow ones

184
00:07:09,330 --> 00:07:11,260
are chrysanthemum crab pastries.

185
00:07:11,390 --> 00:07:13,320
The green ones are mung bean cakes.

186
00:07:15,150 --> 00:07:16,210
And the purple ones

187
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,580
are mashed yam

188
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,200
mixed with grass dragon fruit juice.

189
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,900
What's grass dragon fruit?

190
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,450
Oh, my memory is terrible.

191
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:26,230
In the previous dynasty,
grass dragon fruit was...

192
00:07:26,230 --> 00:07:27,410
It's grape.

193
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:31,310
I always get these two names mixed up.

194
00:07:31,310 --> 00:07:32,000
Seriously,

195
00:07:32,530 --> 00:07:34,790
why do they always change things' names?

196
00:07:37,150 --> 00:07:38,280
Prime Minister Yue.

197
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:39,970
Go.

198
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:42,060
Bring me a clean outfit.

199
00:07:42,580 --> 00:07:44,380
Mine got stained on the way here.

200
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:48,900
Your Majesty.

201
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:49,950
Go ahead.

202
00:07:51,110 --> 00:07:51,870
Don't worry.

203
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:54,030
I don't eat grapes.

204
00:07:54,470 --> 00:07:56,130
And I don't eat people either.

205
00:07:57,740 --> 00:07:58,500
Consort Yue.

206
00:08:00,190 --> 00:08:01,320
It's been a long time

207
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:04,060
since I last tasted your craft brew.

208
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:07,830
But...

209
00:08:07,850 --> 00:08:08,640
Just go.

210
00:08:21,750 --> 00:08:22,750
Miss Jiang,

211
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,620
I didn't expect you

212
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,070
to be so fond of pastries.

213
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:32,250
I come from a different background,

214
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:33,650
so I've seen more.

215
00:08:34,299 --> 00:08:35,549
Miss Jiang,

216
00:08:35,950 --> 00:08:37,880
what are your plans for the future?

217
00:08:39,450 --> 00:08:40,299
Naturally,

218
00:08:40,330 --> 00:08:41,909
to find a goal

219
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,400
and steadily climb upwards.

220
00:08:45,140 --> 00:08:46,140
That makes sense.

221
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,710
But I think

222
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:51,160
the water towns in Jiangnan

223
00:08:51,530 --> 00:08:53,390
are better for long-term living.

224
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:54,980
Why struggle

225
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,360
to climb so hard?

226
00:08:57,970 --> 00:08:59,540
Jiangnan's scenery is beautiful,

227
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:01,140
but it's not like the capital

228
00:09:01,530 --> 00:09:03,620
where dazzling flowers confuse the eyes,

229
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:05,340
blending prosperity and elegance.

230
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:06,660
Who wouldn't love it?

231
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:08,750
Your Majesty,

232
00:09:09,270 --> 00:09:11,600
if you find Jiangnan's scenery so lovely,

233
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,250
why not change your mindset

234
00:09:13,980 --> 00:09:15,260
and move there?

235
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:20,540
Why are you walking so fast?

236
00:09:20,540 --> 00:09:21,460
Slow down.

237
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:30,270
This lantern is pretty cute,

238
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:31,490
just like you.

239
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:35,000
Let me buy it for you as a gift.

240
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,240
It is quite cute.

241
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:37,080
But...

242
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,570
the Mid-Autumn Festival is already over.

243
00:09:38,570 --> 00:09:40,120
What use do I have for a lantern?

244
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,610
Can't I just give you a gift?

245
00:09:41,610 --> 00:09:42,140
Here.

246
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,520
This lantern is so cute.

247
00:09:45,780 --> 00:09:47,810
Ling'er, can I take a look at it?

248
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,030
Sure.

249
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,070
Of course.

250
00:09:54,350 --> 00:09:55,280
It's quite cute.

251
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,080
Yes, it is.

252
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,170
When I was young, I was constantly
on the move

253
00:09:59,170 --> 00:10:00,320
and couldn't afford them.

254
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:01,150
Later, after entering the palace,

255
00:10:01,150 --> 00:10:02,390
I never got to see them again.

256
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:03,750
I always envied others who had them

257
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:04,750
when I was little.

258
00:10:05,550 --> 00:10:06,200
Well...

259
00:10:06,870 --> 00:10:07,600
Yunqing,

260
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:09,270
it's yours now.

261
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,890
Is that alright, Your Majesty?

262
00:10:13,390 --> 00:10:14,960
Alright, Your Majesty?

263
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:21,870
It's okay.

264
00:10:22,150 --> 00:10:23,480
His Majesty will agree.

265
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:24,630
Take it.

266
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:27,140
It looks quite lively over there.

267
00:10:27,140 --> 00:10:28,200
I'll go take a look.

268
00:10:36,620 --> 00:10:38,690
People want a lot of things,

269
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:40,670
but not everything

270
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:42,030
can go their way.

271
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,890
How would you know if you don't try?

272
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:47,850
I once walked a long way

273
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:49,890
and reached a position

274
00:10:49,890 --> 00:10:51,490
I never thought I could.

275
00:10:52,170 --> 00:10:53,570
I suppose that counts...

276
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:55,340
as getting what I wished for.

277
00:11:02,910 --> 00:11:04,910
Then congratulations, Miss Jiang,

278
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:06,750
for having such good luck.

279
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,180
I hope it

280
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:20,550
stays with you.

281
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:29,150
With Your Majesty's blessing,

282
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:31,010
I'm sure I will get what I wish for.

283
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:36,760
Yunqing,

284
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:38,050
what were you...

285
00:11:38,690 --> 00:11:40,020
talking about just now?

286
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,090
Nothing.

287
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:43,020
I was just thanking His Majesty

288
00:11:43,020 --> 00:11:44,140
for this gift.

289
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:45,530
I'll treasure it well.

290
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,210
His Majesty is truly

291
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:48,280
kind

292
00:11:48,550 --> 00:11:49,480
and benevolent.

293
00:11:57,880 --> 00:12:01,270
His Majesty is truly kind and benevolent.

294
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:04,960
Nothing.

